Author: Don King#8901
Content: What is the best way to merge lots of mining utxo into one large utxo? I just tried sending to another address and got an error saying tx was over the size limit. Is there a specific command to merge utxo, or just send in batches is only option?

Author: NutellaLicka#4241
Content:
There sure is. Depending on how many UTXO's you have, you may have to run this a lot of times (I had to run it shitloads and it took hours to merge all of them)
`./komodo-cli -ac_name=PIRATE z_mergetoaddress '["*"]' "yourzaddrhere"`

Author: NutellaLicka#4241
Content: `remainingnotes: x` should tell you how many you've got, and I believe mergetoaddress does 10 at a time (at least in my case)

Author: NutellaLicka#4241
Content: I ran that command like 20times in a row and they just queued up one after another. I monitored the progress with `z_getoperationstatus`

Author: NutellaLicka#4241
Content: Does that answer your question @Don King

Author: Don King#8901
Content: @NutellaLicka , cool man, that looks like what i need, thanks!

Author: ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢#7004
Content:
Dear miners, sellers, and buyers:

In order to create a more cohesive community, that is geared towards promoting a better PIRATE to the rest of the world, I pose the following questions/thoughts:

What do you feel is, or should be, the price determining factor(s) of ARRR?
Hashrate alone? Is 32 cents at 124k diff and 11-15 cents at 40k diff a valid notion?
Does/should KMD/USD have an impact on ARRR/KMD price? Do we, as a community just peg price to KMD no matter what KMD value is?

These are just the base questions I have and hope that the can be answered and prove to springboard into a larger conversation about the true value of PIRATE as well as the perceived monetary value.

Thanks,
CG
